  <description><![CDATA[<p>This bustling city is the region’s largest town and is surrounded by numerous mountains including the Monte Bré and San Salvatore, offering excellent panoramas across Lake Lugano. Rich in culture and with a Mediterranean flair, Lugano is home to colourful parks and interesting architecture. The pedestrianised centre with its boutiques and markets provides great shopping opportunities, whilst the ‘Piazzas’ play host to several events throughout the summer. The promenade is a departure point for many boat trips including to the quaint villages of <em>Gandria</em> and <em>Morcote</em>.</p>]]></description>
