  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<ul>
<li>Cable cars</li>
<li>Cinema</li>
<li>Cycling</li>
<li>Golf</li>
</ul>
<p>Lugano, Switzerland offers many great activities for people on holidays. Public boat services carry visitors to peaceful old fishing villages characterised by tile roofs, pastel-coloured facades and arcades. Undeniably Swiss, but Italian in character, Lugano itself is a small cosmopolitan city with great shopping opportunities from 'old town' markets to Milan-style boutiques. 'Piazzas' with outdoor cafés offer visitors cool drinks after a day spent on the lake, walking in the Verzasca valley, or savouring the views from local mountains Monte San Salvatore and Monte Bre. A free return trip up Monte Bre is included for guests on holidays in Lugano who are staying 5 or more nights and free entrance to the Swiss Miniature Park model village for guests staying 7 nights or more.</p>
<ul>
<li>Free weekly guided tour of ‘Monte Bre’ and funicular, usually Friday afternoons for great views of the city, bay and surrounding area</li>
<li>Several weekly themed guided walks around Lugano including architectural monuments, narrow streets of the town centre and its parks and gardens (many free)</li>
<li>Public lido for lake swimming</li>
<li>Monte Generoso cog railway</li>
<li>Weekly markets with local produce and crafts</li>
<li>'Estival Jazz’ music festival (4-6 Jul)</li>
<li>'Blues to Bop’ music festival (29 Aug - 1 Sep)</li>
<li>Day trips to Lake Maggiore and the botanical gardens of the Brissago islands, and to Lake Como</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Exploring on the Swiss Transport Network<br /></strong></p>
<p>Switzerland’s excellent public transport network of mountain railways, cable-cars, boats and buses makes it a pleasure to explore the sights independently, at your own pace. Some of the excursions below cross the border into Italy.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Half-Price Travel Card worth £80, included for all Inghams guests</strong></p>
<p>Save 50% with your half-price card on unlimited trips of your choice across the Swiss transport network.</p>
<p>Travel card sent to you before departure. Tickets can be pre-booked or many more available locally.</p>
<p>NB. Half-fare card is not valid on Lake Maggiore</p>
<p>Car hire is available </p>]]></thingsToDo>
